416
01:26:50.720 --> 01:26:56.010
John Ellis: Is the context And the token encodings. And then the token embeddings, that's all.

417
01:26:57.270 --> 01:27:00.390
John Ellis: Think of this intelligence as sort of crystalline.

418
01:27:00.550 --> 01:27:01.370
John Ellis: Right?

419
01:27:01.750 --> 01:27:06.930
John Ellis: You add, you recalculate, and you get a new version.

420
01:27:08.120 --> 01:27:14.330
John Ellis: Us were always dynamic, so we thought that intelligence would have to be something that would be dynamic.

421
01:27:14.780 --> 01:27:28.180
John Ellis: I'm a cognitive psychologist. I do mathematical… I did mathematical psychology, and I always thought that it was going to look very different than it is now. So this is one of the reasons why, when we work with AIs, we need to think about it in these terms.

422
01:27:28.910 --> 01:27:31.249
John Ellis: It does not page anthropomorphize.

423
01:27:31.440 --> 01:27:33.040
John Ellis: It's different.

424
01:27:33.180 --> 01:27:36.990
John Ellis: It is a different type of intelligence than we are used to.

425
01:27:37.710 --> 01:27:41.470
John Ellis: The key point For us right now is…

