01:29:47.400 --> 01:29:52.390
John Ellis: And to actually run the tools, and to assess, maybe write the code, it's often writing code.

449
01:29:53.570 --> 01:29:57.380
John Ellis: And then to come back and actually only report back when it is ready.

450
01:29:57.780 --> 01:30:01.690
John Ellis: So this is not a single run, it could actually be done and emit the

451
01:30:02.130 --> 01:30:04.239
John Ellis: End of… end of sequence token.

452
01:30:04.910 --> 01:30:15.410
