01:32:07.250 --> 01:32:24.119
John Ellis: And sometimes you have to turn them on, but it does have computer interaction, it can have its own little, you know, place to write code. Kind of interesting thing, though, right? You don't get to say what libraries are loaded up there, or anything like that, or you can't load anything there, so it's only for its own personal use.

471
01:32:24.500 --> 01:32:36.089
John Ellis: It turns out everybody has adopted skills, and I'll introduce those in a moment. So it has… you almost have to look to see what it has available. So the real caution is, if you use a model, if it has no tools.

