01:34:41.740 --> 01:34:47.110
John Ellis: With a specialized model that did dense, very tight-looped work.

491
01:34:47.490 --> 01:35:04.539
John Ellis: Because think of it, this is what you do, right? If you're going after a topic, you look in this, you see if it leads anyplace else, you assess it to see whether it actually answers or doesn't answer your question, you try to assess it, then you go to the next one. You might actually follow down some of the references here, and then you may stop and say, I'm not seeing anything new.

